    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>Die martis qui fuit decimus exeuntis mensis decembris. <rs
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines">Bonorum virorum</rs> presentia quorum
                        nomina inferius scripta invenientur. <persName
                            key="#childOf #siblingOf #nephew/nieceOf #Landed_possessions #Houses #Cereals #Wine #Fruits/vegetables #Curtes"
                                ><name ref="Boso/f. Ugonis/de Campitello">Boso</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filius</rs> quondam <persName key="#parentOf"><name
                                ref="Hugo/de Campitello">Ugonis</name></persName> de <placeName
                            ref="#places/2489">Campitello</placeName>, una cum <persName
                            key="#uncle/auntOf"><name ref="Gherardus">Girardo</name></persName>, <rs
                            key="#uncle/auntOf">patruo</rs> suo et auctoritate eius, et <persName
                            key="#Slave"><name ref="Malfacientis">Malfacentis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Slave">servus</rs> eius, per se ipse Boso suosque <rs
                            key="#siblingOf">fratres</rs> refutaverunt et finem fecerunt in manu
                        domni <persName key="#Abbots #Monasteries" ref="#people/3568"
                            >Hæinrici</persName>, <rs key="#Abbots">abbatis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Landed_possessions #Houses #Cereals #Wine #Fruits/vegetables #Curtes #Priors #Monks #Altars"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancti Benedicti</orgName> quod est
                        const[r]uctum inter <rs key="#Rivers">flumen</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4196">Padi</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4197">Larionis</placeName>, iuxta flumen
                        ipsius Padi, de tota <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> illa sive <rs
                            key="#Houses">casiva</rs>, sive cum tegis, sive est cum <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>, areis, curtis, <rs key="#Fruits/vegetables">ortis</rs>,
                        sive <rs key="#Cereals">aratoria</rs>, quam ipse Boso cum fratribus suis et
                        predictus Ugo pater eorum dicebant se pro feodo tenere sive aliquo modo in
                        territorio et curte Sancti Benedicti, ab ista parte fluminis Padi, et ab
                        illa parte ipsius fluminis, in <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Landed_possessions #Houses #Cereals #Wine #Fruits/vegetables"
                            ref="#estates/80"><rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs>
                            <placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Landed_possessions #Houses #Cereals #Wine #Fruits/vegetables"
                                ref="#places/362">Vilule</placeName></geogName>, loco qui dicitur
                            <placeName>Seregnano</placeName>, sive aliis locis ipsius curtis, ex
                        parte <persName key="#childOf #parentOf" ref="#people/2199"
                            >Ugonis</persName> filii <persName key="#parentOf" ref="#people/3510"
                            >Manfredi</persName> et <persName key="#childOf #parentOf"
                            >Ubaldi</persName> filii eius atque <persName key="#childOf"
                            >Ugolini</persName> filii ipsius Ubaldi, quę terra erat et est iuris
                        ipsius monasterii Sancti Benedicti. Tali modo finem fecerunt quod ipse Boso
                        eiusque fratres atque Malfacentis servus eorum eorumque heraedes per se vel
                        per summissas personas ipsum monasterium aliquo modo non molestabunt, sub
                        poena <rs key="#Penalty">librarum viginti denariorum Mediolanensium</rs>, et
                        poena saluta taciti tam permanere; et insuper si impedita eidem monasterio
                        fuerit ipse Boso cum suis fratribus eorumque hæredisc expedire et defendere
                        debet. Propter hanc autem refutationem et finem accepit ipse Boso per se
                        suosque fratres <rs key="#Price">libras octo denariorum Mediolanensium</rs>.
                        Actum est hoc <placeName ref="#places/2400">in camera domni
                            abbatis</placeName>. Presentia domni <persName key="#Priors"
                            ref="#people/3570">Wilielmi</persName>, <rs key="#Priors">prioris</rs>
                        ipsius monasterii, et domni <persName><name ref="Benedictus"
                                >Benedicti</name></persName> et domni <persName><name
                                ref="Hugo/de Gurgathelle">Ugonis</name></persName> de
                            <placeName>Gurgathelle</placeName> et domni <persName><name
                                ref="Brochardus">Brochardi</name></persName> et domni
                                <persName><name ref="Hubertus">Uberti</name></persName>, et postea
                        statim in capitulo ante <rs key="#Monks">monachos</rs> ipsius monasterii et
                        insuper supra <rs key="#Altars">altare</rs> Sancti Benedicti. Anno dominice
                        incarnationis millesimo centesimo trigesimo primo, predicto die, inditione
                        nona. Interfuerunt ibi <persName key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness"
                                ><name ref="Robertus/de Gorgo">Robertus</name></persName> de
                            <placeName ref="#places/2403">Gurgo</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness"><name ref="Martinus/Decanus"
                                >Martinus</name></persName> Decanus, <persName><name ref="Mazonus"
                                >Mazonus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness"><name ref="Martinus/Pizolus"
                                >Martinus Pizolus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness"><name
                                ref="Iordanus/de Gherardus Paliarius">Iordanis</name></persName> de
                                <persName><name ref="Gherardus/Paliarius">Girardo
                            Paliario</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness"><name ref="Iohannes/Tosus"
                                >Iohannes Tosus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness"><name ref="Andreas/de Corno"
                                >Andreas</name></persName> de Corno et rogati sunt <rs
                            key="#Witness">testes</rs>. Interfuit <persName key="#Slave"><name
                                ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName> servus ipsius Bosonis. (SN)
                        Ego <persName key="#Notary #Writer" ref="#people/3573">Bonus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> his interfui, rogatus <rs key="#Writer"
                            >scripsi</rs>. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
